{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RBEd9LhYjZjdHwyRGgWQmN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23\n     2→\n     3→### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — verify (2026-03-23T05:45Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\n     6→- **Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running (using `codeharness-shared-*` naming). The `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts. Worked around by using the shared stack directly.\n     7→- **Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path.\n     8→- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find story Status line in the story file — likely looking for `## Status:` pattern that was stripped or mismatched.\n     9→\n    10→### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — create-story (2026-03-23T05:55Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\n    13→- **File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\n    14→- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n    15→\n    16→### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)\n    17→\n    18→- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\n    19→- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\n    20→- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\n    21→\n    22→### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — code-review (2026-03-23T06:07Z)\n    23→\n    24→- **HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\n    25→- **LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` — if tarpaulin outputs `\"coverage\": \"85.5\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\n    26→- **LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\n    27→- **Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n    28→- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\n    29→\n    30→### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — verify (2026-03-23T10:17Z)\n    31→\n    32→- **CLI does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` in JSON output.** `codeharness coverage --json` output includes `tool` but not other `detectCoverageTool()` fields. AC1 and AC2 required supplemental verification by replicating function logic from `dist/index.js`. Documentation/API gap.\n    33→- **AC4 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `parseTestCounts` is internal and not exercised by any CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output. No `codeharness parse-test-output` command.\n    34→- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** No log entries in VictoriaLogs during verification. Expected — container doesn't have Docker-in-Docker so observability stack not running inside it.\n    35→- **Workspace aggregation confirmed.** Bundle shows `parseTestCounts` uses global regex with `matchAll`-style loop for multi-crate workspace test output.\n    36→\n    37→### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — create-story (2026-03-23T09:22Z)\n    38→\n    39→- **Unconditional dependency registry:** Adding `cargo-tarpaulin` means `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on all projects regardless of stack. Fails gracefully (`critical: false`) but is noisy. Stack-conditional filtering would be a separate story.\n    40→- **Pre-existing stub overwritten:** The file already existed as a skeleton from sprint planning. Overwritten with comprehensive story as expected.\n    41→- **Risk: deps-install.test.ts mock registry:** Consumer test mocks `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` with hardcoded single-entry array. Mock isolates consumer from registry changes — no update needed there.\n    42→\n    43→### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — dev-story (2026-03-23T09:28Z)\n    44→\n    45→- **Pre-existing test failures:** 4 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts` when run as full suite — test isolation issue, not related to this story.\n    46→- **Unconditional registry design acknowledged:** `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on non-Rust projects. `critical: false` handles graceful failure. Stack-conditional filtering deferred.\n    47→\n    48→### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — code-review (2026-03-23T09:35Z)\n    49→\n    50→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale — deps.ts description omitted cargo-tarpaulin from tool list.\n    51→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Story File List empty — no files documented in Dev Agent Record.\n    52→- **LOW (not fixed):** Fragile catch-all mock in installAllDependencies tests — implicitly handles cargo-tarpaulin via fallthrough rather than explicit mock branch.\n    53→- Coverage: 97% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor. No gaps.\n    54→\n    55→### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — verify (2026-03-23T09:42Z)\n    56→\n    57→- All 5 ACs passed black-box verification.\n    58→- **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not installed — recurring issue across sessions.\n    59→- **Showboat not installed warning** during `codeharness verify` — non-blocking but means no re-verification via showboat.\n    60→- No observability gaps reported by verifier for this story.\n    61→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484","uuid":"dc111d38-4d4a-4802-ad33-c9608f281cb2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:40:59.462Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23\n\n### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — verify (2026-03-23T05:45Z)\n\n- **Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\n- **Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running (using `codeharness-shared-*` naming). The `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts. Worked around by using the shared stack directly.\n- **Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path.\n- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find story Status line in the story file — likely looking for `## Status:` pattern that was stripped or mismatched.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — create-story (2026-03-23T05:55Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\n- **File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\n- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)\n\n- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\n- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\n- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — code-review (2026-03-23T06:07Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\n- **LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` — if tarpaulin outputs `\"coverage\": \"85.5\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\n- **LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\n- **Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — verify (2026-03-23T10:17Z)\n\n- **CLI does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` in JSON output.** `codeharness coverage --json` output includes `tool` but not other `detectCoverageTool()` fields. AC1 and AC2 required supplemental verification by replicating function logic from `dist/index.js`. Documentation/API gap.\n- **AC4 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `parseTestCounts` is internal and not exercised by any CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output. No `codeharness parse-test-output` command.\n- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** No log entries in VictoriaLogs during verification. Expected — container doesn't have Docker-in-Docker so observability stack not running inside it.\n- **Workspace aggregation confirmed.** Bundle shows `parseTestCounts` uses global regex with `matchAll`-style loop for multi-crate workspace test output.\n\n### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — create-story (2026-03-23T09:22Z)\n\n- **Unconditional dependency registry:** Adding `cargo-tarpaulin` means `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on all projects regardless of stack. Fails gracefully (`critical: false`) but is noisy. Stack-conditional filtering would be a separate story.\n- **Pre-existing stub overwritten:** The file already existed as a skeleton from sprint planning. Overwritten with comprehensive story as expected.\n- **Risk: deps-install.test.ts mock registry:** Consumer test mocks `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` with hardcoded single-entry array. Mock isolates consumer from registry changes — no update needed there.\n\n### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — dev-story (2026-03-23T09:28Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing test failures:** 4 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts` when run as full suite — test isolation issue, not related to this story.\n- **Unconditional registry design acknowledged:** `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on non-Rust projects. `critical: false` handles graceful failure. Stack-conditional filtering deferred.\n\n### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — code-review (2026-03-23T09:35Z)\n\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale — deps.ts description omitted cargo-tarpaulin from tool list.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Story File List empty — no files documented in Dev Agent Record.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Fragile catch-all mock in installAllDependencies tests — implicitly handles cargo-tarpaulin via fallthrough rather than explicit mock branch.\n- Coverage: 97% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor. No gaps.\n\n### 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry — verify (2026-03-23T09:42Z)\n\n- All 5 ACs passed black-box verification.\n- **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not installed — recurring issue across sessions.\n- **Showboat not installed warning** during `codeharness verify` — non-blocking but means no re-verification via showboat.\n- No observability gaps reported by verifier for this story.\n","numLines":61,"startLine":1,"totalLines":61}}}
