{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TnxfzJsrtCXBY4iso3uhFT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Infra module — project initialization, stack management, observability.\n     3→ */\n     4→\n     5→import type { Result } from '../../types/result.js';\n     6→import type { ObservabilityBackend } from '../../types/observability.js';\n     7→import type { InitOptions, InitResult, StackStatus, CleanupResult } from './types.js';\n     8→import { initProject as initProjectImpl } from './init-project.js';\n     9→import { ensureStack as ensureStackImpl, detectRunningStack, detectPortConflicts } from './stack-management.js';\n    10→import { cleanupContainers as cleanupContainersImpl } from './container-cleanup.js';\n    11→import { createObservabilityBackend } from './observability.js';\n    12→\n    13→export type { InitOptions, InitResult, StackStatus };\n    14→export type { InitDockerResult, InitBmadResult, InitBeadsResult, InitDocumentationResult } from './types.js';\n    15→export type { StackDetectionResult, PortConflictResult, CleanupResult } from './types.js';\n    16→// Re-export doc helpers for backward compatibility\n    17→export {\n    18→  generateAgentsMdContent,\n    19→  generateDocsIndexContent,\n    20→  getCoverageTool,\n    21→  getStackLabel,\n    22→  getProjectName,\n    23→} from './docs-scaffold.js';\n    24→\n    25→export async function initProject(opts: InitOptions): Promise<Result<InitResult>> {\n    26→  return initProjectImpl(opts);\n    27→}\n    28→\n    29→export function ensureStack(): Result<StackStatus> {\n    30→  return ensureStackImpl();\n    31→}\n    32→\n    33→export function cleanupContainers(): Result<CleanupResult> {\n    34→  return cleanupContainersImpl();\n    35→}\n    36→\n    37→export { detectRunningStack, detectPortConflicts };\n    38→\n    39→// Dockerfile validation (Story 4.1)\n    40→export { validateDockerfile, loadRules } from './dockerfile-validator.js';\n    41→export type { DockerfileValidationResult, DockerfileGap } from './dockerfile-validator.js';\n    42→\n    43→// Dockerfile template generation (Story 4.2)\n    44→export { generateDockerfileTemplate } from './dockerfile-template.js';\n    45→export type { DockerfileTemplateResult } from './dockerfile-template.js';\n    46→\n    47→export function getObservabilityBackend(config?: {\n    48→  opensearchUrl?: string;\n    49→  opensearch?: { logsIndex?: string; metricsIndex?: string; tracesIndex?: string };\n    50→  victoria?: { logsUrl?: string; metricsUrl?: string; tracesUrl?: string };\n    51→}): ObservabilityBackend {\n    52→  return createObservabilityBackend(config);\n    53→}\n    54→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Us1Yj6kDFpG5rzKPuwN5hF","session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484","uuid":"b04b0b21-3708-4c27-b1d4-bfad0bb4857f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:42:26.699Z"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_progress","task_id":"a951cc0d5081aae0a","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Us1Yj6kDFpG5rzKPuwN5hF","description":"Writing _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-5-rust-dockerfile-template.md","usage":{"total_tokens":56047,"tool_uses":27,"duration_ms":125105},"last_tool_name":"Write","uuid":"73db8cf6-6a79-4fb7-808b-2163ed26b894","session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018PsCj8q64mESqoGnh7voNf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TFTGwowp4EBbUfaiYQtm7x","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-5-rust-dockerfile-template.md","content":"# Story 8.5: Rust Dockerfile template generation\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer deploying a Rust project,\nI want codeharness to generate a multi-stage Dockerfile,\nso that I get a minimal runtime image with just the compiled binary.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **AC1:** Given a Rust project (stack = `'rust'`) without a Dockerfile, when `generateDockerfileTemplate('/project', 'rust')` is called, then it writes a Dockerfile and returns `ok({ path: '/project/Dockerfile', stack: 'rust' })` — NOT `'generic'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n2. **AC2:** Given the generated Rust Dockerfile content, when inspected, then it contains a multi-stage build: a `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder` stage and a `FROM debian:bookworm-slim` runtime stage <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n3. **AC3:** Given the generated Rust Dockerfile content, when inspected, then the builder stage includes `cargo build --release` and the runtime stage uses `COPY --from=builder` to copy the compiled binary <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n4. **AC4:** Given the generated Rust Dockerfile content, when inspected, then the runtime stage installs `curl` and `jq` via `apt-get install`, runs as a non-root user, and includes `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*` cache cleanup <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n5. **AC5:** Given a Rust project with an existing Dockerfile, when `generateDockerfileTemplate()` is called, then it returns `fail('Dockerfile already exists')` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n6. **AC6:** Given the generated Rust Dockerfile, when `validateDockerfile()` is called against it, then it passes all 6 rule categories with zero gaps <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n7. **AC7:** Given `codeharness init` runs on a Rust project without a Dockerfile, when the Dockerfile template generation phase executes, then it generates a Rust-specific Dockerfile (not generic) <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Add `rustTemplate()` function to `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n  - [ ] 1.1 Create `rustTemplate(): string` that returns a multi-stage Dockerfile\n  - [ ] 1.2 Builder stage: `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder`, `WORKDIR /app`, `COPY Cargo.toml Cargo.lock* ./`, `COPY src/ src/`, `RUN cargo build --release`\n  - [ ] 1.3 Runtime stage: `FROM debian:bookworm-slim`, `apt-get install curl jq`, `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*`, `COPY --from=builder /app/target/release/<binary> /usr/local/bin/`, `USER nobody`, `WORKDIR /workspace`\n  - [ ] 1.4 Include inline section comments matching existing template style (`# Base image`, `# Build`, `# System utilities`, `# Install binary`, `# Run as non-root`)\n- [ ] Task 2: Add `'rust'` branch to `generateDockerfileTemplate()` (AC: #1)\n  - [ ] 2.1 In the if/else chain (lines 99-108), add `else if (stack === 'rust')` BEFORE the generic fallthrough\n  - [ ] 2.2 Set `content = rustTemplate()` and `resolvedStack = 'rust'`\n- [ ] Task 3: Update existing test that asserts `'rust'` → `'generic'` (AC: #1)\n  - [ ] 3.1 In `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` line 167, change the `'rust'` test to expect `stack: 'rust'` instead of `stack: 'generic'`\n  - [ ] 3.2 Move the `'rust'` test from the generic describe block into a new `describe('generateDockerfileTemplate — rust')` block\n- [ ] Task 4: Add Rust-specific template tests (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n  - [ ] 4.1 Test: generates Dockerfile with `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder` and `FROM debian:bookworm-slim`\n  - [ ] 4.2 Test: includes `cargo build --release` in builder stage\n  - [ ] 4.3 Test: includes `COPY --from=builder` to copy compiled binary\n  - [ ] 4.4 Test: includes `curl` and `jq` verification tools\n  - [ ] 4.5 Test: includes `USER nobody` for non-root execution\n  - [ ] 4.6 Test: includes apt cache cleanup\n  - [ ] 4.7 Test: includes inline section comments\n- [ ] Task 5: Add Rust template validation compliance test (AC: #6)\n  - [ ] 5.1 Add a test in the `generated Dockerfiles pass validateDockerfile()` describe block\n  - [ ] 5.2 Generate Rust template, feed to `validateDockerfile()`, assert `passed: true` and `gaps: []`\n- [ ] Task 6: Run full test suite — zero regressions\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Current Code Structure\n\n`src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` (119 lines) has:\n- `nodejsTemplate()` → single-stage, `FROM node:22-slim`, `npm install -g` from tarball\n- `pythonTemplate()` → single-stage, `FROM python:3.12-slim`, `pip install` from wheel\n- `genericTemplate()` → single-stage, `FROM node:22-slim`, placeholder\n- `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)` → if/else chain: `'nodejs'` → `'python'` → else (generic)\n\nThe Rust template is different: it needs a **multi-stage** build (builder + runtime). This is because Rust compiles to a static binary — no runtime needed beyond the OS.\n\n### Multi-Stage Dockerfile Template\n\nThe Rust template must use `COPY --from=builder` which is how the `checkBinaryOnPath()` validator detects binary installation (line 90 of `dockerfile-validator.ts`). This is critical for AC6 — without `COPY --from=`, the validator will report a gap.\n\nSuggested template content:\n\n```dockerfile\n# === Builder stage ===\nFROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy manifests first for dependency caching\nCOPY Cargo.toml Cargo.lock* ./\nCOPY src/ src/\n\n# Build release binary\nRUN cargo build --release\n\n# === Runtime stage ===\nFROM debian:bookworm-slim\n\n# System utilities for verification\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl jq && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# Install compiled binary from builder\nCOPY --from=builder /app/target/release/myapp /usr/local/bin/myapp\n\n# Run as non-root user\nUSER nobody\n\nWORKDIR /workspace\n```\n\nNote: The binary name `myapp` is a placeholder. Users must update it to their actual binary name from `Cargo.toml`. This matches how `genericTemplate()` uses `placeholder`. Do NOT attempt to read `Cargo.toml` at generation time — the template is a starting point.\n\n### Validator Compatibility (AC6)\n\nThe 6 rule categories in `dockerfile-validator.ts`:\n1. **pinned-from**: `rust:1.82-slim` and `debian:bookworm-slim` both have version tags — passes\n2. **binary-on-path**: `COPY --from=builder` triggers the regex on line 90 — passes\n3. **verification-tools**: `curl` and `jq` in `apt-get install` line — passes\n4. **no-source-copy**: Template copies `src/` in the BUILDER stage, but the validator regex checks for `COPY src/` at the top level. The builder stage `COPY src/ src/` line will match the validator's `COPY src/` pattern. **IMPORTANT**: Either (a) use `COPY . .` in the builder stage instead of `COPY src/ src/`, or (b) verify that `COPY --from=` prefix exempts the match. Looking at the regex: `/COPY\\s+(?:--\\S+\\s+)*src\\//i` — this matches `COPY src/` but also `COPY --from=builder src/`. The builder stage line is just `COPY src/ src/` (no `--from=`) so it WILL match and trigger a gap. **SOLUTION**: Use `COPY . .` in the builder stage instead. This copies Cargo.toml + src in one layer and avoids the validator false positive.\n5. **non-root-user**: `USER nobody` — passes\n6. **cache-cleanup**: `rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*` — passes\n\n### Corrected Template (Avoiding Validator False Positive)\n\n```dockerfile\n# === Builder stage ===\nFROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy project files\nCOPY . .\n\n# Build release binary\nRUN cargo build --release\n\n# === Runtime stage ===\nFROM debian:bookworm-slim\n\n# System utilities for verification\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl jq && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# Install compiled binary from builder\nCOPY --from=builder /app/target/release/myapp /usr/local/bin/myapp\n\n# Run as non-root user\nUSER nobody\n\nWORKDIR /workspace\n```\n\nThis passes all 6 validator rules. The `COPY . .` in the builder stage does NOT trigger `no-source-copy` because the validator looks for `COPY src/` specifically, and `COPY . .` doesn't match that pattern.\n\n### Breaking Change in Existing Test\n\nLine 164-172 in `dockerfile-template.test.ts` tests that `'rust'` produces `'generic'`:\n```typescript\nit('generates generic Dockerfile when stack is unknown', () => {\n    mockExistsSync.mockReturnValue(false);\n    const r = generateDockerfileTemplate('/project', 'rust');\n    expect(r.success).toBe(true);\n    if (r.success) {\n      expect(r.data.stack).toBe('generic');\n    }\n  });\n```\n\nThis test MUST be updated — it will fail once the Rust branch is added. Move it to its own describe block and change the assertion to `expect(r.data.stack).toBe('rust')`. Replace the generic-unknown test with a different unknown stack (e.g., `'java'`).\n\n### Architecture Constraints\n\n- **<300 line limit**: `dockerfile-template.ts` is 119 lines. Adding ~30 lines for `rustTemplate()` + ~4 lines for the branch = ~153 lines. Well within limit.\n- **No new npm dependencies**: Pure string template. No TOML parsing.\n- **NFR5**: Follows existing `Result<T>` pattern and `DockerfileTemplateResult` type. No type changes needed.\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — the ONLY source file to modify\n- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` — test file to update (334 lines currently)\n- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts` — read-only reference for validator rules\n- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — already calls `generateDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, stack)` at line 78. When `stack === 'rust'`, it will now get the Rust template instead of generic. No changes needed.\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts#L82-118 — generateDockerfileTemplate function]\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts#L21-74 — existing template functions (nodejs, python, generic)]\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts#L164-172 — existing test that maps rust→generic (MUST UPDATE)]\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts#L271-333 — validation compliance tests (ADD RUST)]\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts#L86-95 — checkBinaryOnPath accepts COPY --from=]\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/dockerfile-validator.ts#L116-127 — checkNoSourceCopy regex patterns]\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/init-project.ts#L78 — generateDockerfileTemplate called during init]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-rust-stack-support.md#FR4 — requirement]\n\n### Previous Story Intelligence (8-4)\n\n- 8-4 added cargo-tarpaulin to dependency registry. Test suite had ~2980 tests. Zero regressions.\n- 8-4 only touched `deps.ts` and `deps.test.ts` — no file overlap with this story.\n- Mocking pattern in dockerfile-template tests uses `vi.mock('node:fs')` at top level with `vi.mocked()` wrappers — follow this pattern.\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commits: 4e805b9 (8-4 verified), ebaddac (8-3 verified), d6a76bf (8-2 verified).\nAll Rust stories so far: `stack-detect.ts`, `state.ts`, `coverage.ts`, `deps.ts` + tests.\nThis story only touches `dockerfile-template.ts` and its test file — clean isolation.\n\n### Do NOT Duplicate\n\n- Story 4-2 (`4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration`) created the original `dockerfile-template.ts` with nodejs/python/generic. This story EXTENDS it with Rust.\n- Story 8-6 will create `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` (the VERIFICATION Dockerfile). Do NOT create verification templates here — only the deployment template.\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/8-5-rust-dockerfile-template.proof.md`)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/8-5-rust-dockerfile-template.md`\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n{{agent_model_name_version}}\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### File List\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1085,"cache_read_input_tokens":54161,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1085,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Us1Yj6kDFpG5rzKPuwN5hF","session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484","uuid":"e8e66a68-2a0e-4f33-9703-88927c7ed4c2"}
