{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014z88G1K6TyyZykuwQijwiv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014zLjjUQm6Se5w8uexLt58U","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/codeharness-verify-8-5-rust-dockerfile-template/verify-prompt.txt","content":"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The `src/` directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details. If you cannot verify a feature from docs + CLI alone, that is a REAL failure in the product's documentation or packaging.\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading `README.md` in this workspace. It contains install and usage instructions for the project. Use it to understand how to exercise the CLI.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file `story.md` contains the acceptance criteria you must verify. Read `story.md` now.\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion, you must:\n\n1. Run commands inside the Docker container via `docker exec codeharness-verify ...`\n2. Capture the command output as evidence\n3. Query observability endpoints if runtime evidence is needed\n4. For ACs that involve Claude Code sessions or agent workflows, use `docker exec codeharness-verify claude ...` to spawn real sessions inside the container\n\n### Docker Container\n\n- Container name: `codeharness-verify`\n- ALL CLI commands MUST run via: `docker exec codeharness-verify <command>`\n- Example: `docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness --version`\n- Example: `docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness init --json`\n\nThe container has the following tools installed:\n- `codeharness` — the project CLI\n- `claude` — Claude Code CLI (authenticated via ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var)\n- `curl`, `jq` — for querying observability endpoints\n- `showboat` — for proof document validation\n- `node`, `npm` — Node.js runtime\n\n### Verification Strategy for This Story\n\nThis story is about Rust Dockerfile template generation. The key function is `generateDockerfileTemplate()` which is internal to the codeharness CLI. To verify:\n\n- Use `docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness init` in a temp directory with a Cargo.toml to trigger Rust stack detection and Dockerfile generation\n- Inspect the generated Dockerfile content for multi-stage build, cargo build, COPY --from, curl/jq, USER nobody, cache cleanup\n- Use `docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness audit` to check Dockerfile validation passes\n- For AC5 (existing Dockerfile), create a Dockerfile first then run init again\n\n### Observability Endpoints\n\nQuery these from the HOST (not inside the container) for runtime evidence:\n\n- **VictoriaLogs** (logs): `http://localhost:9428`\n  - Example: `curl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&limit=10'`\n- **VictoriaMetrics** (metrics): `http://localhost:8428`\n  - Example: `curl 'http://localhost:8428/api/v1/query?query=up'`\n- **VictoriaTraces** (traces): `http://localhost:16686`\n  - Example: `curl 'http://localhost:16686/api/traces?service=codeharness-verify&limit=10'`\n\n## Step 3.5: Observability Check After Each Command\n\nAfter EACH `docker exec` command you run, query the observability backend for log events from the last 30 seconds:\n\n```bash\ncurl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'\n```\n\n- If the response contains one or more log entries, note the count in your proof.\n- If the response contains zero log entries, include: `[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction`\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: `verification/8-5-rust-dockerfile-template-proof.md`\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\n```text\n## AC N: <description>\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n```\n\n```output\n<actual output>\n```\n\n**Verdict: PASS | FAIL | [ESCALATE]**\n```\n\n**IMPORTANT: Only use `bash` and `output` as code fence languages.** Never use bare ``` fences without a language tag.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. **ALL commands MUST use `docker exec codeharness-verify ...`** — do NOT run commands directly on the host filesystem.\n2. **Do NOT attempt to access source code** — there is no `src/` directory in this workspace.\n3. **Report REAL failures** — if a feature does not work, report that as a verification failure. Do NOT fabricate passing evidence.\n4. **Every AC needs functional evidence** — reading docs alone is not evidence.\n5. **Verify aggressively, escalate narrowly.** Never blanket-escalate.\n6. **[ESCALATE] is ONLY for things genuinely impossible to automate** — physical hardware, paid external services, human visual judgment. Infrastructure problems are NOT valid escalation reasons.\n7. **Never switch to unit-testable verification.** If Docker verification doesn't work, report WHY as a [FAIL].\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":134,"cache_read_input_tokens":56884,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":134},"output_tokens":55,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484","uuid":"a90bc602-c422-4281-b16a-bae78f0ff954"}
