{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UuNQVzfRC9Q373WyUN2Czc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-23\n     2→\n     3→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n     4→**Session window:** ~09:08 - 09:46 UTC+4 (~38 minutes)\n     5→**Ralph iterations:** 2 (iteration 1 timed out at 30 minutes)\n     6→**Commits produced:** 3\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## 1. Session Summary\n    11→\n    12→| Story | Outcome | Commits | Notes |\n    13→|-------|---------|---------|-------|\n    14→| 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection | done | `4c7f498` | Rust stack detection, app type inference from Cargo.toml |\n    15→| 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust | done (in sprint-status.yaml), verifying (in state-snapshot) | `9ddd65e`, `d6a76bf` | Needed a fix commit for AC2 (rust_env_hint in OTLP state) |\n    16→\n    17→Two stories attempted, two completed. Epic 8.1 (Rust Detection Foundation) is complete. Ralph timed out on iteration 1 after 30 minutes — it completed 8-1 impl+verify plus 8-2 impl+verify but was mid-retrospective when the timer expired. Iteration 2 picked up and produced the verification commit for 8-2.\n    18→\n    19→---\n    20→\n    21→## 2. Issues Analysis\n    22→\n    23→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n    24→\n    25→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n    26→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n    27→| HIGH | 8-1 | `[dev-dependencies]`/`[build-dependencies]` deps incorrectly matched as production deps — false positive server/agent detection | Yes — added `getCargoDepsSection()` |\n    28→| HIGH | 8-1 | Substring false positives on crate names (`anthropic` matching `anthropic-sdk`, `rocket` matching `sprocket`) | Yes — added `hasCargoDep()` with word-boundary regex |\n    29→| HIGH | 8-2 | `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack — Rust projects got wrong default | Yes |\n    30→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | `[[bin]]` and `[lib]` matched inside TOML comments | Yes — used line-anchored regexes |\n    31→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | Missing test coverage for 3 of 5 web frameworks (rocket, tide, warp) | Yes — tests added |\n    32→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | Missing test for `[lib]` + `[[bin]]` dual-crate pattern | Yes |\n    33→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `detectCoverageTool()` had no rust branch — Cargo.toml projects fell to `'unknown'` | Yes |\n    34→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `getStackLabel('rust')` returned `'Unknown'` — AGENTS.md mislabeled Rust projects | Yes |\n    35→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `generateAgentsMdContent()` had no rust branch — Rust projects got \"No recognized stack\" boilerplate | Yes |\n    36→| LOW | 8-1 | `getCargoDepsSection()` does not handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection TOML style | No — accepted per NFR4 |\n    37→| LOW | 8-2 | Duplicate stack-to-tool mapping in `getCoverageTool()` (docs-scaffold.ts) and `getDefaultCoverageTool()` (state.ts) | No — tracked as tech debt |\n    38→\n    39→### Workarounds / Tech Debt Introduced\n    40→\n    41→- **Cargo.toml parsing uses string matching, not a proper TOML parser.** Deliberate per NFR4 (no new deps), but `[dependencies.foo]` subsections and comments containing dep names are edge cases that remain unhandled.\n    42→- **Library crates map to `generic` AppType** rather than a dedicated `'library'` type. Libraries are indistinguishable from unknown projects.\n    43→- **`coverage.tool` type was tightened** from plain `string` to a union type. Non-breaking but undocumented migration — existing state files with unexpected string values would still typecheck at runtime.\n    44→\n    45→### Verification Gaps\n    46→\n    47→- **8-2 AC2 initially failed.** The `rust_env_hint` field was missing from OTLP state for Rust projects. Required a separate fix commit (`9ddd65e`) before the verification commit (`d6a76bf`).\n    48→- **State snapshot still shows 8-2 as `verifying`**, while sprint-status.yaml shows `done`. Sync drift.\n    49→- **~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors** in test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, etc.). Tests pass at runtime via Vitest despite `tsc --noEmit` errors. These are unrelated to this session but create noise during verification.\n    50→- **`parseCoverageReport` has no `'tarpaulin-json'` parser** — out of scope for 8-2, deferred to story 8-3."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019cCP5UbMAnJmty9sqKS4GB","session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484","uuid":"63fb3ff2-ffee-447e-a0c8-c03c01df0086","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:05:24.683Z"}
