{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HW9fjTKudNqSvt4vETZqDV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01X7H8APLPqRA84U35LbsJCy","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-23.md","offset":288,"limit":100},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4167,"cache_read_input_tokens":17915,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4167,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":68,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019cCP5UbMAnJmty9sqKS4GB","session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484","uuid":"71d57ce4-ac47-4c93-9b9e-17a5f93f1229"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X7H8APLPqRA84U35LbsJCy","type":"tool_result","content":"   288→| LOW | 8-3 | No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` (string vs number) | Low risk, `?? 0` handles `undefined` |\n   289→| LOW | 8-3 | `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` in check-only mode | Pre-existing pattern across all stacks |\n   290→| LOW | 8-1 | `getCargoDepsSection()` does not handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection TOML | Accepted per NFR4 (no TOML parser dep) |\n   291→| LOW | 8-2 | Duplicate stack-to-tool mapping in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `state.ts` | Tech debt tracked |\n   292→\n   293→### Workarounds / Tech Debt Introduced\n   294→\n   295→1. **ESM mocking workaround:** `vi.mock('node:child_process', ...)` with file-level mock and `mockReset()` in `afterEach`. Cannot use `vi.spyOn` on `execSync` in ESM mode. Fragile if new tests are added without understanding mock scope.\n   296→2. **Cargo test regex ordering is load-bearing:** Must appear before pytest regex to avoid false matches. No guard comment or ordering test.\n   297→3. **`coverage.ts` now exceeds 600 lines** (architecture limit is 300). Deliberately deferred splitting.\n   298→4. **Cargo.toml parsing is string-based** (no TOML parser). Edge cases with inline subsections and comments remain.\n   299→\n   300→### Verification Gaps\n   301→\n   302→- **8-3 AC1/AC2 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `codeharness coverage --json` does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` fields. The verifier had to replicate `detectCoverageTool()` logic from `dist/index.js` to confirm output. This is a CLI/API gap -- internal functions are not fully exercisable through the CLI.\n   303→- **8-3 AC4 verified via function replication.** `parseTestCounts` is internal with no CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output.\n   304→- **Branch coverage at 77.98%** on `coverage.ts` (below 80% floor). Pre-existing untested branches, not caused by new code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n   305→- **No observability data during verification.** VictoriaLogs received no events during any verification run. Docker container lacks Docker-in-Docker, and `codeharness init` does not emit structured telemetry.\n   306→\n   307→### Tooling / Infrastructure Problems\n   308→\n   309→| Problem | Impact | Recurring? |\n   310→|---------|--------|------------|\n   311→| Leftover `codeharness-verify` container from previous session | Wasted cleanup time at start of verification | Yes (3rd session in a row) |\n   312→| Docker naming mismatch (`codeharness-shared-*` vs compose names) | False \"stack down\" reports, port conflicts | Yes (known since Epic 7) |\n   313→| `codeharness sync` broken (can't find Status line in story files) | Story file statuses stuck at `ready-for-dev` | Yes (broken 9+ epics) |\n   314→| Ralph iteration 1 timed out at 30 min | Lost retro work, required regeneration | First occurrence with 2-story load |\n   315→| State tracking desync between `sprint-status.yaml` and `sprint-state.json` | Ambiguous story status between files | Yes (every session) |\n   316→\n   317→---\n   318→\n   319→## 3. What Went Well\n   320→\n   321→- **Three stories completed in a single session.** Epic 8.1 fully done. First story of Epic 8.2 done. Sprint progress moved from 25/34 to 28/34.\n   322→- **Self-review caught 10 bugs before verification.** The pattern of implementation followed by code review before verification continues to be the highest-ROI quality gate. The HIGH bug in `parseTestCounts` (workspace aggregation) would have been a runtime defect.\n   323→- **97% test coverage on 8-1.** All 123 files above 80% floor. 2980 tests passing, zero regressions.\n   324→- **Session issues log worked as designed.** Each subagent appended real issues as they encountered them. This file was the raw material for all three retrospective addenda.\n   325→- **Docker verification for 8-3 succeeded on first attempt** in iteration 4, despite the story being complex (internal functions not directly CLI-exercisable).\n   326→\n   327→---\n   328→\n   329→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   330→\n   331→- **Iteration 1 timeout.** 30-minute budget was insufficient for implementing, verifying, and retro-writing two stories. The retro was killed mid-write, wasting tokens and requiring regeneration.\n   332→- **8-2 AC2 failed first verification pass.** `rust_env_hint` was missed in the initial implementation. Required a separate fix commit and re-verify cycle.\n   333→- **8-3 verification deferred across iterations.** Code review completed in iteration 3 but verification didn't run until iteration 4. The story spent ~40 minutes in limbo between `verifying` and `review` status across different tracking files.\n   334→- **Docker infrastructure friction consumed time in every iteration.** Container naming mismatch, leftover containers, and port conflicts are recurring problems that have not been fixed.\n   335→- **`codeharness sync` is still broken.** This has been a known issue for 9+ epics. Story file statuses are permanently stuck at `ready-for-dev`. At this point it's actively harmful -- it creates noise in every session and gives false confidence to anyone reading story files.\n   336→\n   337→---\n   338→\n   339→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   340→\n   341→### Repeat\n   342→\n   343→- **Self-review before verification.** Found 10 bugs across 3 stories before any verification run. This is consistently the best quality investment.\n   344→- **Track issues in `.session-issues.md` as they happen.** Having timestamped raw materials made retrospectives possible even after iteration timeouts.\n   345→- **Separate fix commits from feature commits.** Clean git history makes debugging straightforward.\n   346→- **Session retro addenda pattern works.** Appending to the retro file after each iteration gives progressive visibility without losing earlier analysis.\n   347→\n   348→### Avoid\n   349→\n   350→- **Do not schedule retro writing inside the same iteration budget as implementation.** Iteration 1 proved this -- the retro was killed mid-write. Retros should be a dedicated short iteration or run outside Ralph.\n   351→- **Do not trust `codeharness status --check-docker`.** Docker naming mismatch makes output unreliable. Use `docker ps` directly.\n   352→- **Do not let `coverage.ts` grow further without splitting.** It is 2x the architecture limit (600+ lines vs 300) and branch coverage is degrading. The next story touching this file must split it.\n   353→- **Do not defer fixing recurring infrastructure issues.** Docker naming mismatch and `codeharness sync` breakage have been noted in retrospectives for 9+ epics. Each session wastes time on the same workarounds.\n   354→\n   355→---\n   356→\n   357→## 6. Action Items\n   358→\n   359→### Fix Now (before next session)\n   360→\n   361→- [ ] Reconcile `sprint-state.json` -- set 8-3 status to `done` to match `sprint-status.yaml`\n   362→- [ ] Clean up leftover Docker containers (`codeharness-verify`, duplicates)\n   363→- [ ] Verify `state-snapshot.json` has 8-2 and 8-3 both as `done`\n   364→\n   365→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   366→\n   367→- [ ] **Split `coverage.ts`** into separate modules (Rust, Node, Python parsers). 600+ lines, 2x the 300-line limit. Branch coverage already degrading.\n   368→- [ ] **Fix Docker container naming** -- align `codeharness status --check-docker` with `codeharness-shared-*` convention. This has wasted time every session since Epic 7.\n   369→- [ ] **Add guard comment or ordering test** for cargo-test/pytest regex precedence in coverage parsing\n   370→- [ ] **Extract duplicate `stack -> coverage_tool` mapping** into a single utility function (duplicated in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `state.ts`)\n   371→- [ ] **Add `rust_env_hint` to init-time telemetry** (observability gap -- no VictoriaLogs events during Rust project init)\n   372→- [ ] **Expose `runCommand` and `reportFormat` in CLI JSON output** -- `codeharness coverage --json` currently omits these fields, forcing verification to replicate internal function logic\n   373→\n   374→### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   375→\n   376→- [ ] Fix `codeharness sync` story status header pattern matching (broken 9+ epics, noted in every retro)\n   377→- [ ] Fix ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files\n   378→- [ ] Handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline TOML subsection style in `getCargoDepsSection()`\n   379→- [ ] Add `'library'` AppType for Rust `[lib]`-only crates instead of mapping to `generic`\n   380→- [ ] Add type validation to `parseTarpaulinCoverage` for string vs number coverage values\n   381→- [ ] Write integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` output parsing (not just mocked)\n   382→- [ ] Add `parseTestCounts` CLI subcommand for direct test output parsing (currently internal-only)\n   383→\n   384→---\n   385→\n   386→## Session Metrics\n   387→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019cCP5UbMAnJmty9sqKS4GB","session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484","uuid":"b63cd06a-71fb-4be5-9d7b-8d0da38cd6ac","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:05:41.497Z"}
