{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GLUcpA83Cp2CkMNGkydgG2","type":"tool_result","content":"   435→\n   436→---\n   437→\n   438→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   439→\n   440→### Bugs Discovered and Fixed (5 HIGH, 7 MEDIUM)\n   441→\n   442→| Severity | Story | Issue | Status |\n   443→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   444→| HIGH | 8-3 | `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line -- workspace projects emit one per crate | Fixed -- global regex + aggregation loop |\n   445→| HIGH | 8-1 | `[dev-dependencies]`/`[build-dependencies]` deps incorrectly matched as production deps | Fixed -- `getCargoDepsSection()` |\n   446→| HIGH | 8-1 | Substring false positives on crate names (`anthropic` matching `anthropic-sdk`) | Fixed -- `hasCargoDep()` with word-boundary regex |\n   447→| HIGH | 8-2 | `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack | Fixed |\n   448→| HIGH | 8-4 (pre-existing) | 4 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts` when run as full suite -- test isolation issue | Not fixed, pre-existing |\n   449→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | `[[bin]]` and `[lib]` matched inside TOML comments | Fixed -- line-anchored regexes |\n   450→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | Missing test coverage for 3 of 5 web frameworks | Fixed -- tests added |\n   451→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `detectCoverageTool()` had no rust branch | Fixed |\n   452→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `getStackLabel('rust')` returned `'Unknown'` | Fixed |\n   453→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `generateAgentsMdContent()` had no rust branch | Fixed |\n   454→| MEDIUM | 8-4 | AGENTS.md stale -- deps.ts description omitted cargo-tarpaulin from tool list | Fixed |\n   455→| MEDIUM | 8-4 | Story File List empty -- no files documented in Dev Agent Record | Fixed |\n   456→\n   457→### Known Issues NOT Fixed (accepted risk)\n   458→\n   459→| Severity | Story | Issue | Reason |\n   460→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   461→| LOW | 8-3 | No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` (string vs number) | Low risk |\n   462→| LOW | 8-3 | `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` in check-only mode | Pre-existing pattern |\n   463→| LOW | 8-1 | `getCargoDepsSection()` does not handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection TOML | Accepted per NFR4 |\n   464→| LOW | 8-2 | Duplicate stack-to-tool mapping in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `state.ts` | Tech debt tracked |\n   465→| LOW | 8-4 | Fragile catch-all mock in `installAllDependencies` tests -- handles cargo-tarpaulin via fallthrough | Accepted |\n   466→| LOW | 8-4 | Unconditional `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` on non-Rust projects -- noisy but graceful (`critical: false`) | Stack-conditional filtering deferred |\n   467→\n   468→### Workarounds / Tech Debt Introduced This Session\n   469→\n   470→1. **ESM mocking workaround (8-3):** `vi.mock('node:child_process', ...)` with file-level mock and `mockReset()` in `afterEach`. Cannot use `vi.spyOn` on `execSync` in ESM mode.\n   471→2. **Cargo test regex ordering is load-bearing (8-3):** Must appear before pytest regex to avoid false matches. No guard comment or ordering test.\n   472→3. **`coverage.ts` exceeds 600 lines (8-3):** Architecture limit is 300. Deliberately deferred splitting. Branch coverage now at 77.98% (below 80% floor).\n   473→4. **Cargo.toml parsing is string-based (8-1):** No TOML parser per NFR4. Edge cases with `[dependencies.foo]` subsections remain.\n   474→5. **Unconditional dependency registry (8-4):** `cargo-tarpaulin` is installed on all projects regardless of stack. Fails gracefully but generates noise.\n   475→6. **Pre-existing test isolation failure (8-4):** 4 tests in `state.test.ts` fail in full-suite mode. Not addressed.\n   476→\n   477→### Verification Gaps\n   478→\n   479→- **8-3 AC1/AC2 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `codeharness coverage --json` does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` fields. Verifier replicated internal logic from `dist/index.js`.\n   480→- **8-3 AC4 verified via function replication.** `parseTestCounts` is internal with no CLI subcommand.\n   481→- **Branch coverage at 77.98%** on `coverage.ts` (below 80% floor). Pre-existing, not caused by new code.\n   482→- **No observability data during any verification.** VictoriaLogs received no events. Docker containers lack Docker-in-Docker.\n   483→- **8-4 showboat not installed.** `codeharness verify` warning about missing showboat. Non-blocking.\n   484→\n   485→### Tooling / Infrastructure Problems\n   486→\n   487→| Problem | Impact | Recurring? | Sessions affected |\n   488→|---------|--------|------------|-------------------|\n   489→| Leftover `codeharness-verify` container | Cleanup time at session start | Yes | 3+ sessions |\n   490→| Docker naming mismatch (`codeharness-shared-*` vs compose) | False \"stack down\", port conflicts | Yes | Since Epic 7 |\n   491→| `codeharness sync` broken (Status header pattern) | Story file statuses permanently stale | Yes | 9+ epics |\n   492→| Ralph iteration 1 timeout at 30 min | Lost retro work mid-write | Occasional | This session |\n   493→| State tracking desync (sprint-status vs sprint-state vs state-snapshot) | Ambiguous story status | Yes | Every session |\n   494→| `bd` binary not installed | Beads sync fails silently | Yes | 3+ sessions |\n   495→| Showboat not installed | No re-verification option | Yes | This session |\n   496→\n   497→### State Tracking Desync (Detailed)\n   498→\n   499→This session ended with three tracking files disagreeing on 8-4 status:\n   500→- `sprint-status.yaml`: 8-4 = `done`\n   501→- `sprint-state.json`: 8-4 = `review` (should be `done`)\n   502→- `.state-snapshot.json`: 8-4 = `backlog` (stale, not updated by iteration 5)\n   503→\n   504→Similarly, `.state-snapshot.json` shows 8-3 as `verifying` and sprint done count as 27, while `sprint-state.json` shows 8-3 as `done` and count as 28. The snapshot file is clearly stale from an earlier iteration.\n   505→\n   506→---\n   507→\n   508→## 3. What Went Well\n   509→\n   510→- **Four stories completed in one session.** Epic 8.1 and Epic 8.2 both fully done. Sprint at 85% completion.\n   511→- **Self-review caught 12 bugs before verification.** 5 HIGH, 7 MEDIUM across 4 stories. The pattern of code-review before verification continues to be the single most effective quality gate.\n   512→- **8-4 completed cleanly.** All 5 ACs passed black-box verification on first attempt. 97% overall test coverage, all 123 files above 80% floor.\n   513→- **Session issues log worked as designed.** Every subagent appended issues as encountered. The log was the raw material for this and all prior retrospective addenda.\n   514→- **Progressive retro addenda pattern.** Each iteration produced or updated the retro, giving visibility even when iterations timed out.\n   515→\n   516→---\n   517→\n   518→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   519→\n   520→- **Iteration 1 timeout.** 30-minute budget was insufficient for 2 stories + retro. Retro killed mid-write, had to be regenerated in iteration 2.\n   521→- **State tracking is fundamentally broken.** Three files (`sprint-status.yaml`, `sprint-state.json`, `.state-snapshot.json`) all disagree on story statuses. No reconciliation mechanism exists. This has been true every session and is getting worse as more stories complete.\n   522→- **Docker infrastructure friction in every verification.** Container naming mismatch, leftover containers, and port conflicts are recurring costs. Noted in retros since Epic 7 with no fix.\n   523→- **`codeharness sync` has been broken for 9+ epics.** Every retro since Epic 0 mentions this. At this point the feature is non-functional and actively wastes attention.\n   524→- **8-4 dependency registry is unconditional.** `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` runs on Node.js and Python projects. Graceful failure, but noisy and wasteful.\n   525→- **Pre-existing test isolation failures.** 4 tests in `state.test.ts` fail in full-suite mode. Carried forward without fix.\n   526→\n   527→---\n   528→\n   529→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   530→\n   531→### Repeat\n   532→\n   533→- **Self-review before verification.** 12 bugs found across 4 stories. This is consistently the highest-ROI quality investment. Do not skip it.\n   534→- **Track issues in `.session-issues.md` in real time.** Timestamped raw materials made all retro addenda possible, even after timeouts."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019cCP5UbMAnJmty9sqKS4GB","session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484","uuid":"08c3d418-fd6a-470a-97c0-567779cc9a7a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:05:49.300Z"}
