{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017wQzjQkmWyY62hkKkXHx4G","type":"tool_result","content":"   534→- **Track issues in `.session-issues.md` in real time.** Timestamped raw materials made all retro addenda possible, even after timeouts.\n   535→- **Separate fix commits from feature commits.** Git history stays clean and debugging verification failures is straightforward.\n   536→- **Progressive retro addenda.** Appending after each significant iteration gives incremental visibility without blocking on a final pass.\n   537→\n   538→### Avoid\n   539→\n   540→- **Do not rely on state file consistency.** Three tracking files (`sprint-status.yaml`, `sprint-state.json`, `.state-snapshot.json`) diverge every session. Treat `sprint-status.yaml` as source of truth; treat the others as stale caches.\n   541→- **Do not defer Docker naming fix any longer.** This is the 5th+ retro noting the same problem. The workaround cost compounds every session.\n   542→- **Do not add to `coverage.ts` without splitting first.** At 600+ lines (2x the 300-line limit) with branch coverage below floor, the file is a maintenance liability. Next story touching it must refactor.\n   543→- **Do not schedule retrospective inside the same timeout as implementation.** Budget retro writing as a separate, short iteration.\n   544→\n   545→---\n   546→\n   547→## 6. Action Items\n   548→\n   549→### Fix Now (before next session)\n   550→\n   551→- [ ] Reconcile `sprint-state.json` -- set 8-4 status to `done` to match `sprint-status.yaml`\n   552→- [ ] Reconcile `.state-snapshot.json` -- update 8-3 to `done`, 8-4 to `done`, sprint done count to 29\n   553→- [ ] Clean up leftover Docker containers (`codeharness-verify`, duplicates)\n   554→\n   555→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   556→\n   557→- [ ] **Split `coverage.ts`** into Rust/Node/Python parser modules. 600+ lines, 2x the 300-line limit, branch coverage degrading.\n   558→- [ ] **Fix Docker container naming** -- align `codeharness status --check-docker` with `codeharness-shared-*`. Wasting time every session since Epic 7.\n   559→- [ ] **Add stack-conditional filtering to dependency registry** -- `cargo-tarpaulin` should only install for Rust projects.\n   560→- [ ] **Add guard comment or ordering test** for cargo-test/pytest regex precedence.\n   561→- [ ] **Extract duplicate `stack -> coverage_tool` mapping** into single utility (duplicated in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `state.ts`).\n   562→- [ ] **Expose `runCommand` and `reportFormat` in `codeharness coverage --json`** -- internal fields not accessible via CLI, forcing verification to replicate logic.\n   563→- [ ] **Add `rust_env_hint` to init-time telemetry** -- observability gap, no VictoriaLogs events during Rust init.\n   564→- [ ] **Fix 4 pre-existing test isolation failures** in `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts`.\n   565→\n   566→### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   567→\n   568→- [ ] Fix `codeharness sync` story status header pattern matching (broken 9+ epics, noted in every retro)\n   569→- [ ] Fix ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files\n   570→- [ ] Handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline TOML subsection style in `getCargoDepsSection()`\n   571→- [ ] Add `'library'` AppType for Rust `[lib]`-only crates\n   572→- [ ] Add type validation to `parseTarpaulinCoverage` for string vs number values\n   573→- [ ] Write integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` output parsing (not just mocked)\n   574→- [ ] Add `parseTestCounts` CLI subcommand for direct test output parsing\n   575→- [ ] Install `bd` binary so beads sync can function\n   576→- [ ] Install showboat for re-verification capability\n   577→\n   578→---\n   579→\n   580→## Session Metrics (Final)\n   581→\n   582→| Metric | Value |\n   583→|--------|-------|\n   584→| Stories completed | 4 (8-1, 8-2, 8-3, 8-4) |\n   585→| Stories failed | 0 |\n   586→| Bugs found pre-verification | 12 (5 HIGH, 7 MEDIUM) |\n   587→| Bugs shipped unfixed | 0 HIGH/MEDIUM, 6 LOW (accepted) |\n   588→| Ralph iterations | 5 |\n   589→| Timeouts | 1 (iteration 1) |\n   590→| Commits | 4 |\n   591→| Total test count | 2980+ passing |\n   592→| Sprint progress | 25/34 -> 29/34 (85% done) |\n   593→| Epics completed this session | 2 (Epic 8.1, Epic 8.2) |\n   594→| Remaining backlog | 5 stories (Epic 8.3-8.5) |\n   595→| Recurring issues unfixed | 5 (Docker naming, sync, state desync, test isolation, coverage.ts size) |\n   596→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019cCP5UbMAnJmty9sqKS4GB","session_id":"daf25720-e009-4a3c-8a3c-df9d68d99484","uuid":"9684be71-0d44-4e77-805e-ea4218c1f003","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:05:56.479Z"}
